// ==========================================
// MANDATORY IRC COMMANDS (ft_irc project)
// ==========================================

// ---------- CONNECTION / REGISTRATION ----------

// PASS <password>
// Sent before registration. Must match the password passed to ./ircserv
// Example:  PASS mySecret
// Error if sent after registration (ERR_ALREADYREGISTRED 462)

// NICK <nickname>
// Sets or changes the nickname.
// Example:  NICK yle-jaou
// You must check duplicates and reply with 433 if nick already in use.

// USER <username> <mode> <unused> :<realname>
// Second part of registration after NICK.
// Example:  USER mariam 0 * :Mariam Lby
// When both NICK + USER + PASS are received => send 001 welcome.

// QUIT [:message]
// Disconnects the user gracefully. Broadcast quit message to shared channels.
// Example:  QUIT :Leaving

// PING <token>
// Server should reply with PONG <token>.
// Example:  PING 12345
// Reply:    PONG 12345

// PONG <token>
// Client’s reply to your server’s PING. Optional to handle but should be accepted.


// ---------- CHANNEL & MESSAGING COMMANDS ----------

// JOIN <channel>{,<channel>} [<key>{,<key>}]
// Join or create a channel. Create it if it doesn’t exist.
// Example:  JOIN #general
//           JOIN #locked password123
// On success, send JOIN, NAMES, and TOPIC replies.

// PART <channel>{,<channel>} [<message>]
// Leave one or more channels.
// Example:  PART #general :goodbye everyone

// PRIVMSG <target> :<message>
// Send a private message to a channel or user.
// Example:  PRIVMSG #general :Hello world
//           PRIVMSG Mariam :hey, you there?

// NOTICE <target> :<message>
// Same as PRIVMSG but must not generate auto-replies.
// Example:  NOTICE #staff :Maintenance soon.


// ---------- CHANNEL MANAGEMENT (OPER COMMANDS) ----------

// MODE <channel> [<modestring> [<mode params>]]
// Change or view modes for a channel.
// Example:  MODE #general +i        // set invite-only
//           MODE #general -i        // remove invite-only
//           MODE #general +k key123 // set password
// Required modes (from subject):
//   i — invite-only
//   t — topic restricted to operators
//   k — set/remove channel key (password)
//   o — give/remove operator privilege
//   l — set/remove user limit

// TOPIC <channel> [:<topic>]
// View or set a channel topic.
// Example:  TOPIC #general
//           TOPIC #general :Welcome to the general chat!
// Respect +t mode (only ops can change when set).

// INVITE <nick> <channel>
// Invite a user to a channel (required for +i channels).
// Example:  INVITE mariam #private

// KICK <channel> <user> [<comment>]
// Eject a user from a channel (must be channel operator).
// Example:  KICK #general mariam :spamming


// ---------- OPTIONAL BUT RECOMMENDED ----------

// CAP LS / CAP END
// Capability negotiation. irssi sends CAP LS at connect.
// Reply: :<server> CAP * LS :
// Ignore CAP REQ and CAP END safely.

// ERROR :<message>
// Sent by server before closing a connection with an error message.


// ---------- NUMERIC REPLIES (examples you should send) ----------
// 001 <nick> :Welcome to the IRC network
// 433 * <nick> :Nickname is already in use
// 461 <nick> <cmd> :Not enough parameters
// 462 <nick> :You may not reregister
// 401 <nick> <target> :No such nick/channel
// 403 <nick> <channel> :No such channel
// 442 <nick> <channel> :You're not on that channel
// 482 <nick> <channel> :You're not channel operator
